column5: Terry, lol!

From ice fishing to river fishing. The  transition is so easy. LOL  I know this time of year, the waters are high,dirty and cold. It,s a hit or miss gamble on where I hit. Seems my gamble paid. Water was prime, IMO. Bright pink nickle bags were the ticket. Managed to go 3-5 and kept one for my old friend, as I do from time to time. The MOJO rod was on fire.
Congratulations on a successful Outing !
nice going
